verbose_text: Consistent with the phenotypes of both affected mothers, mild neurodevelopmental phenotypes accompanied by language and motor delay were present in the majority of the 38 unrelated probands : 6% of the individuals had normal IQ levels (85-100), 14% had borderline ID (IQ 70-85), and from the 72% diagnosed with ID (IQ < 70), most had mild ID (IQ 50-70) (XREF_FIG).
